Preconditions:
The input matrix must not be null.
The input matrix must be a square matrix, i.e., the number of rows must be equal to the number of columns.
Each row and column of the matrix must be sorted in ascending order.

Postconditions:
The method should return an integer value representing the kth smallest element in the matrix.
The returned value should be one of the elements present in the matrix.
The matrix should remain unchanged after the method is executed.